response:
The total number of jelly beans in the bag is 5 + 6 + 7 + 8 = 26, and since all jelly beans are equally likely to be selected, we can calculate the probability of selecting a blue jelly bean by dividing the number of blue jelly beans by the total number of jelly beans.
</think>
(answer)
\begin{align*}
\text{Probability of selecting a blue jelly bean} &= \frac{\text{Number of blue jelly beans}}{\text{Total number of jelly beans}}\\
&= \frac{8}{26}\\
&= \boxed{\frac{4}{13}}
\end{align*}

