To simplify this, we first condense the nested roots by applying the exponent rules.
\begin{align*}x \sqrt{x} &= \sqrt{x} \cdot \sqrt{x} \cdot \sqrt{x}\\& = x^{3/2}\end{align*}

\begin{align*}\root 3 \of {x^{3/2}}&= \left( x^{3/2} \right)^{1/3}\\&= x^{1/2}\end{align*}

\begin{align*}\root 3 \of {x \root 3 \of {x \root 3 \of {x^{1/2}}}}&= \root 3 \of {x \root 3 \of {x \cdot x^{\frac {1}{6}}}}\\&= \root 3 \of {x \cdot x^{\frac {7}{6}}}\\&= \root 3 \of {x^{\frac {13}{6}}}\\&= x^{\frac {13}{18}}\end{align*}
That is, our expression, in its simplest form! Notice that this is a must-know for the AMC tests.
